title: Alphabet Inc. Cl A stock outperforms competitors on strong trading day
text:
Shares of Alphabet Inc. Cl A 
        GOOGL,
        +0.04%
       inched 0.40% higher to $150.67 Tuesday, on what proved to be an all-around grim trading session for the stock market, with the S&P 500 Index 
        SPX,
        +0.11%
       falling 0.28% to 5,203.58 and Dow Jones Industrial Average 
        DJIA,
        +0.12%
       falling 0.08% to 39,282.33. Alphabet Inc. Cl A closed $3.11 below its 52-week high ($153.78), which the company reached on January 29th. The stock outperformed some of its competitors Tuesday, as Microsoft Corp. 
        MSFT,
        -0.17%
       fell 0.29% to $421.65, Amazon.com Inc. 
        AMZN,
        +0.31%
       fell 0.78% to $178.30, and Meta Platforms Inc. 
        META,
        -1.68%
       fell 1.42% to $495.89. Trading volume (21.9 M) remained 10.9 million below its 50-day average volume of 32.9 M.
